&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retrieve Adult Critical Care Transfer Service – Duty Consultant roles to March 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sessional (2+ operational shifts + 1 non-resident on-call per month) to staff 12/7 rota in each operational base&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for consultants in Intensive Care Medicine and / or Anaesthesia working in hospitals within the South West Critical Care Network to join &lt;em&gt;Retrieve&lt;/em&gt;, the South West Adult Critical Care Transfer Team hosted by University Hospitals Bristol and Weston NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic, experienced and enthusiastic consultants to co-ordinate, undertake and remotely supervise adult critical care transfers as well as contribute to &lt;em&gt;Retrieve&lt;/em&gt; education, training, clinical governance and outreach programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The minimum commitment is 2 operational shifts per month (10am to 10pm) and 1 non-resident on-call shift delivering decision-support, triage and coordination of transfers for the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are two operational base locations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peninsula Base located at Launceston Minor Injury Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Severn Base located at Southmead Hospital in Bristol&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is looking to recruit consultants rapidly for an initial period to 31st March 2021 and is anticipated to launch in late October 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Scott GrierJob titleLead ConsultantTelephone number07764 756739Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peninsula Base Lead Dr David Ashton-Cleary at ubh-tr.retrieve@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
